title: Nightly build got `ONNX export failed` error while running "super_resolution_with_caffe2.ipynb" tutoria
body_html:
Issue description

I tested with nightly build

pip install torch_nightly -f https://download.pytorch.org/whl/nightly/cu90/torch_nightly.html

and tried to run tutorial super_resolution_with_caffe2.ipynb, then got the following error

/home/ubuntu/anaconda3/envs/pytorch_p36/lib/python3.6/site-packages/torch/onnx/utils.py:500: UserWarning: ONNX export failed on ATen operator pixel_shuffle because torch.onnx.symbolic.pixel_shuffle does not exist
  .format(op_name, op_name))
RuntimeError: ONNX export failed: Couldn't export operator aten::pixel_shuffle

Both ONNX 1.2.1 and 1.3 worked for pytorch 0.4.1 when running this tutorial.

Code example

https://github.com/pytorch/tutorials/blob/gh-pages/_downloads/super_resolution_with_caffe2.ipynb

# Input to the model
x = torch.randn(batch_size, 1, 224, 224, requires_grad=True)

# Export the model
torch_out = torch.onnx._export(torch_model,             # model being run
                               x,                       # model input (or a tuple for multiple inputs)
                               "super_resolution.onnx", # where to save the model (can be a file or file-like object)
                               export_params=True)      # store the trained parameter weights inside the model file

System Info

I usded AWS deep learning AMI ubuntu Conda V14 p2.16xlarge to test.
